external_knowledge:
- 'captains' in the context of the metaphor refer to the users who are involved in the actions;
- 'ships' represent the environments where actions are performed;
- 'sea regions' refer to the parent environments which group the environments;
- 'best courses' are determined by the performance metrics, with higher values indicating better performance;
- 'treasures' symbolize the actions (update, delete, create) that the users have performed on the configuration parameters within their respective environments;
- 'top 3' means the environments that rank highest in performance within their parent environments.
